manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: High absorption vegan multivitamin & multimineral for women with iron, methylated folate & B12, zinc, vitamin D3 & K2 Pure & Essential Advanced Multivitamin and Minerals with Iron is a high-absorption multi-nutrient supplement formulated to provide comprehensive nutritional support for women. This vegan formula features highly bioavailable and active forms, allowing nutrient levels to be effectively raised in the body for superior benefits. Enhanced with sustained release technology, this supplement steadily releases nutrients into the bloodstream for all-day nutrient coverage. Expertly formulated by Igennus nutrition scientists with effective doses and balanced nutrient ratios, this supplement works in harmony with the body. It complements and tops up the diet, so it is safe to take long term. Designed to support overall physical and mental wellbeing, we have elevated doses of vitamin D, iron, zinc, B6 & B12 for enhanced coverage for energy levels, immunity, hormonal balance and mood.

Advanced nutrient forms enhanced with slow release Methylated & active B-vitamin complex Especially important for those with the MTHFR genetic variants, this multivitamin contains active b-vitamin forms: Folate, not folic acid: provides the body-ready form of folate, as L-[6S]-5-methyltetrahydrofolate (most standard supplements contain folic acid)Vitamin B6 as pyridoxal-5-phosphate with cofactor activityVitamin B12 as methylcobalamin, for enhanced uptake Chelated iron, zinc & copper This supplement contains 14mg iron in the well-absorbed bisglycinate form that is gentle on the stomach. Providing 100% of the NRV (nutrient reference value) for women, this formula is especially suitable for women of menstruating age to maintain iron levels. We use fully reacted and chelated zinc glycinate and the optimally absorbed copper glycinate chelate. As zinc and copper compete for absorption in the body, this formula contains an optimal ratio to keep the body in balance for long-term health maintenance. Bioavailable vitamin D3 & K2 While there are two forms of vitamin D, vitamin D3 (cholecalciferol) is better absorbed and utilised and is significantly more biologically effective than vitamin D2 (ergocalciferol). Vitamin K2 contributes to bone formation and redirects calcium from the arteries into bones; we use Menaquinone-MK-7 (all-trans not cis) which has better bioavailability and is retained in the body longer than any other form of vitamin K.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 26, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Finally a multi that doesn’t make me sick!
reviews.reviewText: I stopped taking multivitamins because I would always get nauseated and feel sick- sometimes even throw up after taking them, especially on an empty stomach. These multis are wonderful! I can take them on an empty stomach with no side effects whatsoever. They are easy to swallow. They do leave your mouth with a slightly icky vitamin taste but it goes away quickly. I don’t think there are many vitamins out there that don’t do that though. I do believe these have methylated B vitamins, which are the only kind I can absorb. I am vegan so I had been looking high and low for a vitamin with methylated B and Iron that was vegan friendly. These are great but I do wish they came in a bigger bottle. I run out fast.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2021
reviews.reviewText: There are a lot of reviews speaking about the taste and smell of these vitamins. I don't know about you but I don't really choose my vitamins based on the way they taste or smell. I buy based on the ingredients and effectiveness of the product. I'm not going to lie, these smell and taste awful but, they are made that way because the company chose to jam pack the pills with actual vitamins and minerals as opposed to fillers and I'm okay with that. I can deal with a minute or two of unpleasant taste and smell to be healthier, in the long run.I recently started on Keto and decided I needed to supplement with a multivitamin. I tried another brand specifically for keto that majorly upset my stomach. I have a tendency to be sensitive to vitamins and some medications. I was worried that this might do the same but, I have been taking the full dose for three days now with no ill effects.Tonight I got an email from the company with a guide to taking this supplement and answers to some FAQs which I thought was pretty awesome.Overall, for the price and quality of the product, so far, I feel like it can't be beat. If you can get over the smell and taste, I definitely would recommend taking a shot on these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect blend of nutrients, right proportions, with correct form (as bio absorble derivatives)
reviews.reviewText: The size is perfect for easy swallowing besides being non-GMO VEGETARIAN. It is packed with the right combination of vitamins and minerals in the right proportion in the most desirable bio-absorbable form. This product distinguishes itself from others in this respect. They provide some of the b vitamins (pyridoxin and riboflavin) as phosphate derivatives instead of nitrate or other derivatives. B12 is provided in a methylated form which is most potent without side effects. Phosphates are more readily bio absorbed and thus very effective. Zinc is another ingredient which helps immunity against pathogens. The other minerals : molybdenum, chromium, copper, boron etc. are very beneficial as well. I have a suggestion for them: Please include manganese which is a trace mineral because recent studies have shown that manganese can reverse atherosclerosis. There are very few supplements to reverse atherosclerosis and manganese would be really a boon to anyone with arterial stenosis. And please come up a supplement for men without so much iron and added manganese

reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars I cannot continue these.
reviews.reviewText: I don't know how well they actually work or how beneificial they actually are. I only took them for a single month (to not waste money). I saw no benefits of them, but it's a multivitamin and unless you are deficient and taking them for at least a few months I suppose you wouldn't see any improvements physically or mentally... HOWEVER... they smell SO terrible. They make me nauseous because of how badly they smell. So, while I DID take them and saw no positive nor adverse reactions to them, the stink (which permeates the bottle) means I won't be purchasing again.I'd like to note I do have sensory processing disorder so that may play a large role in it. But, if you have aversions to strong smells, I'd suggest staying away from these.

The product is 5 star. It's high quality and I like that the team is extremely researched. The buyer SHOULD NOTE that taking on iron isn't always a good thing. This particular product has EXTRA IRON. I have been taking these supplements for over 2 years now and I have accumulated EXCESS iron. This is a dangerous condition because the body doesn't simply dump iron. I need to perform regular phlebotomy to get rid of the excess iron I have accumulated in my body.Before taking any supplements, perform a DETAILED blood panel. The one your general doctor gives you and says "you are healthy as a horse" is not enough! You need more data before putting things into your body. Learn from my mistake.
Llevo unos meses tomando las pastillas y parece que funciona yo tenía anemia y con tratamiento y estas vitaminas he mejorado muy rápido

L'ho ricomprato perchè sicuramente come contenuto di minerali è il migliore che ho trovato su amazon. Non molti sanno leggere le etichette a quanto pare. Altrimenti saprebbero che la forma di B12 meticolbalamina di questo integratore è molto meglio della cianocobalamina, in genere tossica e presente negli integratori comuni, per giunta in quantità esagerata (che predispone al cancro al polmone). Per non parlare del metilfolato rispetto all'acido folico che, per essere utilizzato dal corpo in forma di folato, deve passare attraverso numerose reazioni, mentre i folati sono subito metabolizzati nel piccolo intestino. Oltre a non essere immediatamente disponibile per l’utilizzo, l’acido folico può diventare pericoloso quando si accumula: diversi studi l’hanno associato ad un aumentato rischio di cancro al colon.Quantità ottima pure di selenio rispetto ai soliti integratori.E poi il mio preferito: il glicinato di zinco invece dei soliti ossido, gluconato o citrato che sono meno biodisponibili e che danno enorme nausea.Se pensate che tutti i minerali e vitamine siano uguali, sappiate che non è così e la qualità in base alla loro forma è molto diversa.Inutile andare sul risparmio e acquistare prodotti inefficaci e dannosi, altrimenti si perde il senso stesso dell'integrazione. Allora a quel punto meglio non prender nulla!Io direi che questo prodotto vale il suo prezzo e anche di più, ricordiamo infatti che le compresse sono molte. Peccato solo per l'assenza del Magnesio
